[2] Georgia (Dade County)
Date: Tue 12 Mar 2013
Source: 11 Alive.com [edited]
http://www.11alive.com/news/article/282519/40/Bats-with-deadly-disease-found-in-Ga


The Georgia Department of Natural Resources said Tuesday [12 Mar 2013] that bats with a deadly disease have been found in 2 Dade County, Georgia, caves.

Several tri-colored bats with white nose syndrome were found in Lookout Mountain Cave at Chickamauga and Chattanooga National Military Park, and in Sittons Cave at Cloudland Canyon State Park.

White nose syndrome is named for a white fungus that coats the muzzles, ears, and wings of infected bats, according to Georgia DNR [Department of Natural Resources] wildlife biologist Trina Morris. The disease is deadly to bats and has killed millions of them in the eastern US.

Morris said there is no evidence white nose syndrome infects humans, but people have carried spores of it out of caves on their clothing or gear.

[byline: Beth Sawicki]

