The state of Georgia can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at http://healthmap.org/r/5UO3. Dade County in north west Georgia can be seen on the map at http://www.digital-topo-maps.com/county-map/georgia.shtml.

[A photo of tri-color bats (_Perimyotis subflavus_) may be viewed at http://www.batcon.org/index.php/all-about-bats/species-profiles.html?task=detail&species=2345&country=43&state=all&family=all&start=25.

Indeed, it has been a roll call of affected states and provinces, and now we add 2 more states to the list of those affected with WNS.

This is an extremely devastating disease and seems to be simply wiping out the bat population. While some good news is that tiny hints of recovery may be occurring, the bad news is by far overshadowing the tiny hints. To add to the bad news is that science is batting its proverbial head against a brick wall at finding a cure for this disease. While there are things being tried, it certainly seems to be baby steps. - Mod.TG]
